OverTheWire Bandit – Level 31 → Level 32 

Level Goal
A git repository is hosted at:
 ssh://bandit31-git@bandit.labs.overthewire.org/home/bandit31-git/repo on port 2220.
The password for user bandit31-git is the same as the password for bandit31.

Commands Used
git clone
ls
cat

Steps
SSH into the Bandit server.
Use the bandit31 password to connect as user bandit31-git:
  ssh bandit31-git@bandit.labs.overthewire.org -p 2220
Clone the repository located at /home/bandit31-git/repo:
  git clone ssh://bandit31-git@bandit.labs.overthewire.org:2220/home/bandit31-git/repo
Navigate into the cloned repository directory:
  cd repo
List files and inspect contents to find the password for bandit32:
  ls -la
  cat <file-containing-password>

Result
 Successfully obtained the password for bandit32 from the cloned git repository.

What I Learned
How to connect to remote git repositories over SSH with custom ports.
Using git clone to download and explore repository contents.
Searching for important data hidden in git repositories during security challenges.
